"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-24-rapper-snoop-dogg-to-carry-olympic-torch-ahead-of-opening-ceremony\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Famous American rapper, Calvin Cordozar Broadus Jr, popularly known as Snoop Dogg will be carrying the Paris Olympic flame in the final stretch ahead of the opening ceremony.  The opening ceremony will take place on Friday, July 26, 2024, with over 10,000 athletes on boats on the Seine River.  Before the ceremony kicks off, the rapper will carry a torch through the Paris suburb Saint-Denis, the town mayor, Mathieu Hanotin confirmed on his official X.  The mayor wrote; \\\"Saint Denis: last step before the Eiffel Tower. An international cast @SnoopDogg for the last stretch of the Olympic Flame.\\\"  Other carriers of the torch include French rapper MC Solaar and French actress Laetitia Casta.  'Harassment from gays made me quit female character' - Skit maker, Josh2funny  War: Angelina Jolie's dad slams her for supporting Palestine  I lost my sight after smoking with Snoop Dogg - Ed Sheeran  Snoop Dogg, Mike Tyson, Rod Wave, others to attend Trump's presidential inauguration  Snoop Dogg names his top 3 rappers of all time  FIBA Ranking:  D'Tigress climb to eighth position after impressive Olympic outing  Snoop Dogg, Billie Eilish to perform at Olympic closing ceremony  Paris 2024: D'Tigress stun Australia with first Olympic win 20 years  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"